==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Connate-perfoliate
<hw>Con"nate-per*fo"li*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Connate or coalescent at the base so as to
produce a broad foliaceous body through the center of which the stem
passes; -- applied to leaves, as the leaves of the boneset.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Connation</ent>⟦br⟧
